  "prompt": "How can I know that I am not in the friend zone?",
  "response": "Determining whether you are in the \"friend zone\" can be a bit tricky, but there are some signs and behaviors that can help you gauge the situation. Here are some indicators that you might **not** be in the friend zone:\n\n### 1. **They Show Romantic Interest**\n   - They flirt with you, compliment you, or make physical contact (e.g., touching your arm, hugging, or sitting close).\n   - They initiate conversations or plans with you frequently.\n\n### 2. **They Express Jealousy**\n   - They seem uncomfortable or act differently when you mention other people you\u2019re interested in or spending time with.\n\n### 3. **They Include You in Their Future**\n   - They talk about future plans or activities that involve you in a romantic context (e.g., \u201cWe should go on a trip together\u201d or \u201cI\u2019d love to introduce you to my family\u201d).\n\n### 4. **They Open Up Emotionally**\n   - They share personal thoughts, feelings, and vulnerabilities with you, which indicates trust and a deeper connection.\n\n### 5. **They Respond Positively to Advances**\n   - If you subtly express romantic interest (e.g., calling them cute, asking them on a date), they reciprocate or seem excited about it.\n\n### 6. **They Treat You Differently Than Others**\n   - They give you special attention or prioritize you over other friends, which could signal they see you as more than a friend.\n\n### 7. **They Initiate Physical Affection**\n   - They hold your hand, cuddle, or engage in other forms of affectionate touch that go beyond typical friendship behavior.\n\n### 8. **They Confess Their Feelings**\n   - They explicitly tell you they have romantic feelings for you or express interest in a relationship.\n\n---\n\n### Signs You **Are** in the Friend Zone:\n   - They refer to you as a \u201cfriend\u201d or \u201cbuddy\u201d frequently.\n   - They talk to you about their romantic interests in other people.\n   - They don\u2019t reciprocate your flirtatious or romantic gestures.\n   - They avoid or feel uncomfortable when the topic of a romantic relationship comes up.\n   - They treat you the same as they treat their other friends, with no special attention.\n\n---\n\n### What to Do If You\u2019re Unsure:\n1. **Communicate Openly**: Have an honest conversation about your feelings and ask where they stand. It\u2019s better to know than to guess.\n2. **Observe Their Actions**: Sometimes actions speak louder than words. Pay attention to how they treat you compared to others.\n3. **Set Boundaries**: If you\u2019re not okay with being just friends, it\u2019s important to communicate that and make decisions accordingly.\n\nUltimately, mutual interest and clear communication are key to moving beyond the friend zone or accepting the relationship as it is.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
